items.name: Difference ControlNets
items.description:
Original ControlNet Difference Models HuggingFace Repository

STOP! THESE MODELS ARE NOT FOR PROMPTING/IMAGE GENERATION AND ARE FOR USE WITH ANY STABLE DIFFUSION 1.5 BASED MODELS (which are most models unless stated to be SD 2.X) AS CONTROL NETWORKS. THE ONES SHARED AT https://civitai.com/models/9251/controlnet-pre-trained-models ARE ControlNets FOR THE BASE SD 1.5 MODEL ITSELF, NOT DIFFERENCE ONES.

Control Nets allow you to guide the structure of an image based on existing ones and preprocessing them, or by using images that match the expected format for a given control net. More information regarding ControlNet and the different types can be found at https://github.com/lllyasviel/ControlNet.


All examples generated using preprocessors, with the AbyssOrangeMix2 - Hardcore model, with the prompt used being the same as the original input image (but with different seeds). All settings default except where mentioned on a specific control net type. Canvas width set to 512 x 768 to match the input image.


You only need to download the models you want to use, you do not need to download all of them.

These are the models required for the ControlNet extension, converted to Safetensor and "pruned" to extract the ControlNet neural network. I have tested them with AOM2, and they work. Download these models and place them in the \stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-controlnet\models directory.

Diagram was shared by Kohya and attempts to visually explain the difference between the original controlnet models, and the difference ones.

modelVersions.name: Alpha 6.0 Anime
modelVersions.description:
This is the Alpha 6 version in anime style. All images are generated in 2d and 2.5d anime style. This version does NOT draw realistic and semi-realistic. ONLY ANIME, ONLY WAIFUS! The model consists of:

  1. xRikishi's Unstable Diffusion (Alpha version) - Alpha 6.0

  2. Animelike25DV11Pruned

  3. ZensuzHolyShit

Recommendations for use:

  1. Good sketches are obtained with CFG 1-2.5, I recommend using a value 5-13 for the usual anime style.

  2. I recommend using the following samplers:

  • Heuh is the most demanding, but it works in detail with the foreground and background, as well as with fine detail.

  • UniPC is the optimal image creation time, makes clear visible contours and saturated colors.

  • DMP++ 2M SDE Karras is a very demanding sampler, perfectly draws the background and characters.

  1. You can use any anime upscaler for Highres. fix

  2. VAE is already built into the model, but you can use any one you like.

  3. I recommend using at least one negative embedding to improve the quality of the image filling. To avoid the appearance of children's faces and bodies, you can use "loli, kid, children, child, baby, baby face, girl, boy, young" in negative prompt.

items.name: USS Anchorage (Azur Lane)
items.description:
Updated Mar/11/2023:

Tried out the LoHA (LoCon, aka LyCORIS as per its creator's preferred but eccentric name) format for Anchorage's update. Quality is indeed impressive and switching to this training method takes surprisingly little time to adapt to. I strongly recommend other trainers to give it a go.

  • IMPORTANT: This extension for webui from LoHA's creator is required to access LoHA models: https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon. Only then LoHA will be read and function just like any other LoRA model. Place 'em where LoRAs reside, call 'em up the way you call LoRAs up, simple as that. Otherwise you'll get only the vanilla image delivered by checkpoint with errors in the console.

An obvious defect however, is that due to the very high level of details it acquired through training, some features I thought to be unique to her original costume (the chest harness as I noticed) would pop up somewhat more often when not prompted to do so. Not sure if negative prompting could fix this or I need to further refine captioning.

Release V2.0 works well on full weight (1.0) and here are prompts for replicating her original costume. Copy & paste it for ease of use, as skimming chara/outfits into a single keyword is NOT remotely as flexible despite it surely is convenient:

  • acrgazln, very long hair, headgear, blue coat, cleavage, midriff, off shoulder, very long sleeves, sleeves past fingers, short shorts, thigh strap, black footwear,

Features USS Anchorage from Azur Lane in her original costume, trained on ACertainModel.

Release V1 has been tested and works with high level of flexibility on high weight range (0.7-0.9), for lower weight details such as her eye color or harness may become inconsistent.

Suggested Prompts:

  • Base: acrgazln, headgear, blue coat, sleeves past fingers, short black shorts, black footwear

items.description:
v3.5 Update

Two notable changes in this version:
- As requested for a long time now, I've added ducks and other water birds to the training data! Now the lora can do bills! See the "About this version" tab for a list of trained species.

-Compatibility for various models is improved over v3
(Update, v3.5 seems to have more issues with regular wings than past versions did. I will try and improve this in the next update)

v3 Update! The biggest update yet!

- Most importantly, v3 is a standard LoRA so it should now work for any installation without any extra extensions!

-Use "v3 no offset" if your gens looks fried, many popular furry models will work better with that version instead of the base "v3"

- I've added noise offset to the training which gives better color and contrast, this does conflict with some other models and loras, so if you're getting a deep fried result try "v3 no_offset" instead. It has all the same training and data just without the noise offset.

- v3 now contains all of the training data for my other avian loras and more, meaning it can pretty much do everything they can do and more! This has made the lora way more versatile and able to do a lot of types of birds very well.

- Other minor improvements, including cleaned up tags, added tags, improved dataset, better training settings, and some other minor stuff

Tags!
Species: Puffin, Cockatiel, Secretary Bird, Owl, Snow Owl, Barn Owl, Corvid, Crow, Raven, Magpie, Blue Jay, Tweetfur, Griffin, Chicken, Rooster, Hen, Falco, Rito, It can do others but these are the ones specifically trained.

General Tags: Anthro, Avian, Bird, Beak, Wings, winged-arms, wing-hands, Tail Feathers, Talons, Claws, Beakjob

-

I really like bird girls, so I put together a bird LoRA!

The model is capable of male and female, sfw and nsfw.
Use tag winged-arms to get winged arms. Other good tags include bird, avian, tail feathers, beak, and other bird features.
For more consistent winged arms, use "winged-arms" in positive and "wings, hands" in negative prompt. Reverse that if you want wings and regular arms.

- Overall tagging and flexibility of the model is improved!
It does much better winged arms now (better than the old winged arms specific model), and generally gives better detail overall. The improved tagging also helps with males and other weak points of the old version.

- v2 was trained on DivineEleganceMix-v3 and works great with anime models in general. I've tested it with DivineElegance v3, anythingfurry-v1, OrangeMix, Anything-v4.5, MeinaMix, and a few others to great success.

-v1.5 shares all the improvements of v2, but was trained on Furrystaberv4 again. It is still better for models that don't have a lot of anime influence like Furrystaber, Lucid'sMix, and a number of other furry models.

items.name: hyper penetration stomach bulge
items.description:
Update: I've trained a new version with a much better training setup and I also trimmed the dataset and cut it into 3 categories to give much more control over the size and type of bulge, plus one version that includes all 3 sets which I highly recommend mixing in with other versions to improve consistency.

Version Nice: dataset trimmed for images with nicely detailed bulges that aren't ridiculously huge (still pretty big though, I might make another version for better smaller bulges)

Version Absurd: selection of some of the most absurd insertions/penetrations. This one especially benefits from mixing version "All" with it, something like absurd:0.8 all:0.6 will give very consistent outputs. I tried merging them into one lora but every method I tried to do so gave vastly inferior results compared to putting both loras in prompt.

Version Pectoral: images with bulges reaching up to chest. Intended to be for impossible penetrations going right through the chest instead of the stomach bulge extending up to chest level, but it's ambiguous.

Tips: Don't forget to add vaginal/anal, it'll vastly improve the penetration part. Also, I recommend adding fat or pregnant in negative to improve the shape of the bulge.

LORA trained on a large set of images focused on large penetration, more specifically large stomach distention. I tried going for versatility and minimal visual impact. High epochs with high weight can get very weird, I'd recommend starting with epoch 4 and 0.8 or lower weight (v7 seems fine with higher). Even then this is meant for extreme content, if you just want normal large penetration many models can do that very well already.

For more absurdity, try things like absurd stomach bulge, all the way up torso, or ask for sideways viewpoint. I've added a lot of tags to training data, but it doesn't particularly react more strongly to exact tags, just try things. Seems pretty difficult to train a LORA that can react to many specific things like the shape of the stomach bulge, I tried but without much success, at most minimal changes on occasion when forcing it with 1.5+ emphasis. (things like ribbed or spiky dildos, or cone-shaped object insertion)

Combines well with other LORAs, as demonstrated in the last example image. Extreme insertion can improve the penetration part, tentacle bulge gives interesting shape to the bulge, and autofellatio (and maybe other futa ones) helps the AI draw absurd bulges by thinking it might be a dick at first.

items.name: Luna's Khyle Style Lora
items.description:
Trained on Khyle. the popular artist that creates meme like artwork.

This is a 768 resolution Lora. Can it do nudes? Yes... Can it do lewds? Yes.

I did NOT upscale a single image, nor did I use anything but the base model to create my references. I'm sure it can be improved even further with these, but I wanted to show raw output. (I am adding some examples with TI's, the goku and misty one is not with a TI though actually)

There is a large variation in terms of control vs style based on weight. You can get pretty much spot on style at 1.0 weight, but control will dip. The most fun you can have with it is just using it to make random goofy images as the style seems to excel at it. If your hoping to get exactly what yoru prompted you're not gonna get it with this close to a style transfer.

I trimmed several not so great images from the dataset, alone with the ones with too much of a male focus, or that might bias the images too much into producing multiple characters. Also ones that had odd art styles/random real life people in it. Trigger word is khyle, and khyle style. I did some tests and maybe using khyle style gives you better results, but its marginal at best, its mostly just a different gen sometimes.

Will be posting a lower dim version, and possibly adjusted settings to maybe improve control. but honestly its so nearly perfect visually, I kinda don't care

items.name: Kasumi Tendo - Ranma 1/2
items.description:
A bit of nostalgia and a quality old school Waifu only competing with Shampoo and ranma-chan herself in the Ranma 1/2 verse. If someone wants to prove me wrong i will gladly consume any LORA they make :P

V2

Here we are again with the best Tendou sister. It's been a while since i made this LORA. While serviceable, nowdays i prefer to lose some freedom in exchange for repeatability(read as preprogrammed outfits). So I once gain cleaned the dataset. Retouched some extremely crappy images with img2img and the v1 lora. Re-tagged everything and baked it again. Also baked a LOCON version which i'll post in a while.

Seems to work fine using <lora:Tendou_KasumiV2:0.7>, tendou_kasumi, <outfit>

Available outfits are:

  • Apron_White_Ruffle: This one is used in almost all of her outfits except blue dress.

  • Apron_Pinkish_White_Ribbon: this one is exclusive to her blue dress

  • Green_Turtleneck_Shirt_Blue_Skirt: This one is from the ova.

  • Light_Blue_Dress_KSM: This is one of her iconic dresses together with her apron.

  • Yellow_Sweater_Red_Skirt: The other classic outfit

  • Swimsuit_HighLeg_Strapless_Green: swimsuit from nihao my concubine

  • Yellow_Shirt_blue_high-waist_skirt: Another one from the OVAs

  • Bikini_Green_Strapless_HighLeg: From a pool episode i think

  • ovadress: Another from nihao my concubine that movie is really prolific outfit wise.

  • nightgown_KSM: Another one from the OVAs

As Always I will add the dataset so people can experiment.

V1

Got ok-ish results with: highres, 1girl, (Tendou_Kasumi), brown_hair, big_breasts, standing, looking_at_viewer, <lora:Tendou_Kasumi:.7>

Seems that at higher weight levels(.9-1) the low quality of the training images start to shine through.

Gathering the training set was a nightmare and most of it was low res crap, porn or VHS quality screenshots. The original manga was a no go as the style looks weirder and even more dated. Anyway i did my best. I'll add the training data if someone wants to try their hand at it.

items.name: Sombra (Overwatch) LORA
items.description:
Version 2 is overall big improvment. Simply prompting for Sombra will suffice for whole look, except for optional lipstick.

Suitable strength range is 0.6-0.8. Triggers for paticular things, in case you still need them, are:

  • Outfit - bodysuit, coat, trench coat, turtleneck, high collar, legwear, gloves, short sleeves

  • Accesories - jewelry, stud earrings, hologram, holographic interface

  • Makeup - makeup, mascara, eyeshadow, eyeliner, long fingernails, nail polish

  • Gun (really wonky, not trained for it) - holding gun, weapon, submachine gun, finger on trigger

If you liked my work, you can donate here.

Trained on Anything V4.5.

Samples are 512x768, not cherry picked, without HighRes.fix, using OrangeCocoa 50/50 Mix , with OrangeMix VAE (for version 2), and using EasyNegative embedding. Inpaint examples are txt2img with 1 single inpaint done on eyes.
